title: For Sale/Trade:  GERMAN K98 WITH RARE MARKINGS
postcontent:
If only this thing could talk! 1938 dated factory code "42" made by mauser oberndorf which is an original mauser factory and still has mauser banner on stock. The barrel has pitting on outside of barrel and bore is fair and serviceable with minor pitting here and there. This is a pretty collectibke piece but could be used for just about anything. This gun has 2 nazi eagles (dirty birds) on left side of gun-one on barrel and one on receiver and 3 on right side of receiver. All numbers match including stock and bands exect the bolt. 

This rifle is covered in waffenampts on metal and wood. The stock has been hit by shrapnel and i beleive there is a peice stuck in stock still by the floorplate. 

This rifle was used by germans in ww2 and sent to china at some point after the war so this thing has seem ALOT of action! This thing is kinda hard to find info on but ive gathered that germany sold alot of k98s to the chinese and the chinese fought in ww2 against the japs, in korea against US and in vietnam they supplied the vietnamese with weapons. Also it could have been a russian capture and supplied to vietnamese and used there. Its definitely been in a moist environment. But the russian capture idea wouldnt make any sense because the dirty birds are not peened and theres no "X" on receiver. 

My best guess on this gun is that it was sold to china by the germans and supplied to the NVA in vietnam and used there. It would explain the markings and non-peened eagles and pitting. 

In the deal you will be getting the rifle, areproduction leather sling and might throw in a few stripper clios and ammo. Im asking $575. This is a very collectible piece here but could be used for hunting and shooting as well it shoots great! Not a bad price for what it is.
